This paper studies the capacities and the coding strategies for the K-user cyclic Gaussian interference channel in the weak and the strong interference regimes. An achievable rate region based on the Han-Kobayashi power splitting strategy is ﬁrst derived; a corresponding capacity region outer bound is then obtained using genie-aided bounding techniques. This paper shows that in the weak interference regime, the Etkin, Tse and Wang’s power-splitting strategy achieves to within two
bits of the capacity region. The capacity result for the K-user cyclic Gaussian interference channel in the strong interference regime is a straightforward extension of the corresponding two-user case. However, in the mixed interference regime, although the constant gap result may well continue to hold, the proof becomes considerably more complicated, as different mixed scenarios need to be enumerated and the corresponding outer bounds derived.
